---
description: Mid-task session handoff before context exhaustion, or explicit /checkpoint
alwaysApply: false
---
Follow `.claude/skills/context-management/SKILL.md` for a mid-task checkpoint before context
exhaustion, or when the user asks to checkpoint. Claude Code's version is also driven by a
`PreCompact` hook (`.claude/settings.json`); Cursor has no hook system, so this rule is
best-effort — it relies on the agent noticing the conversation is getting long, not a guaranteed
trigger the way the hook is.
